[For 1999, India reported to OIE (Office International des Epizooties)
80 bovine outbreaks with 228 animals affected, and 50 outbreaks
involving sheep and goats with 318 animals affected. I suspect that
these numbers are short. As far as I can tell from my Indian contacts
the national control policy for livestock anthrax is not actively pursued,
and many regional programmes are ineffective. Like most (countries)
they use the Sterne vaccine, which is perfectly adequate when deployed
properly. - Mod.MHJ
